      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "id": "1a8a7077_8b45882d",
      "file_path": "build/creating_data/docker-images-collector.sh",
      "patchset_number": 6,
      "line": 87,
      "message": "yes effort we are here after with these comments. And wanted those groundings to be explained here in the code as it's a quite exotic way to parse information in utility script. Even if how \"native\" it can be in the environment where helm is supposed to be used, it's not at all so native in this kind of script.\n\nAnd now when actually started to thinking the purpose of this script, wonder are we doing this completely wrong way now if trying to collect this list from helm charts?\n\nThere is some process in onap for artifacts versions:\nhttps://wiki.onap.org/display/DW/Independent+Versioning+and+Release+Process\n\nand manifests of version lists both for docker images:\nhttps://git.onap.org/integration/tree/version-manifest/src/main/resources/docker-manifest.csv\n\nand java artifacts:\nhttps://git.onap.org/integration/tree/version-manifest/src/main/resources/java-manifest.csv\n\nShould we base our downloading on those? At least we should have version to support those formats/urls.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 3957,
        "name": "Samuli Silvius",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "s.silvius@partner.samsung.com",
        "username": "silvius"
      },
      "updated": "2019-03-18 13:36:12.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "f07d8a25_743ffe52",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "id": "2e0e646d_99b388c8",
      "file_path": "build/creating_data/docker-images-collector.sh",
      "patchset_number": 6,
      "line": 87,
      "message": "I agree with Samuli the way how it's done here is not pure, but as I said before, so far I haven't found any better way to get the relevant result (all images I want and no remainders).\nAd the process: It looks like the release process doesn't work at all. As you can see the manifest contains images we don't use in our deployments, the versions of those we use are about 3 patch versions behind our 3.0.1 list and there is about 60 images missing (about 30 related to rancher kubernetes).\nFrom my point of view the best would be if the image lists would come from OOM project or the OOM should be more focused to offline, as I doubt there would be any real online deployment (security reasons).",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 5000,
        "name": "Tom�? Levora",
        "display_name": "Tomáš Levora",
        "email": "tomas.levora@gmail.com",
        "username": "Tomas.Levora"
      },
      "updated": "2019-03-18 14:49:12.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "1a8a7077_8b45882d",
      "unresolved": false
    },
